  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Let thy fountain be blessed,.... Thy wife; make her happy by keeping to her and from others; by behaving in a loving, affable, and respectful manner to her; by living comfortably with her, and providing well for her and her children: or reckon her a happiness, a blessing that God has bestowed; or ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "\"thy fountain shall be blessed,'' ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "as the Targum; that is, with a numerous offspring, which was always reckoned a blessedness, and was generally the happiness of virtuous women, when harlots were barren; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and rejoice with the wife of thy youth; taken to be a wife in youth, and lived with ever since; do not despise her, nor divorce her, even in old age, but delight in her company now as ever; carry it not morosely and churlishly to her, but express a joy and pleasure in her; see Ecclesiastes 9:9. Jarchi interprets this of the law learned in youth; but it might be much better interpreted of the pure apostolic church of Christ, \"the beulah\", to whom her sons are married, Isaiah 62:4; to whom they should cleave with delight and pleasure, and not follow the antichristian harlot. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "and rejoice with the wife of thy youth; taken to be a wife in youth, and lived with ever since; do not despise her, nor divorce her, even in old age, but delight in her company now as ever; carry it not morosely and churlishly to her, but express a joy and pleasure in her; see ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Ecclesiastes 9:9",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". Jarchi interprets this of the law learned in youth; but it might be much better interpreted of the pure apostolic church of Christ, \"the beulah\", to whom her sons are married, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Isaiah 62:4",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; to whom they should cleave with delight and pleasure, and not follow the antichristian harlot. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
